    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chests for the safe-keeping of valuables usually made of wood and sheathed in iron, of a type made in the ancient and Medieval periods.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000121792/Richter, Furniture of the Greeks (1966)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Arcones para conservar seguros objetos de valor normalmente hechos de madera y revestidos en hierro; de un tipo fabricado en la antigüedad y en la época medieval.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
